commits.message:
Fix AWS region detection by using the config file (#1107)

This attempts a belt-and-suspenders approach to defining the AWS
region in both an environment variable (AWS_REGION) and the config
file (~/.aws/config, as managed by `aws configure`).

This is necessary because in 29e57fc I tried to simplify region
detection script, but unfortunately failed to realize that `aws
configure get region` won't read the value from the environment
variable.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Skip dockerhub login for dependabot runs (or when token is empty) (#1104)

When dependabot runs, it doesn't have the secrets defined. Let's skip
doing the `docker login` in this case. Since we can't access `secrets`
in an `if` block, we'll have to stash the value into an `env` variable.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Fix OWASP scan by setting `httponly` on device_id cookie (#1103)

This attribute improves security by ensuring that JavaScript cannot
tamper with this cookie. It was already encrypted and signed anyway, so
that wouldn't be easy, but I suppose this is one extra layer of defense.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Add dependabot config for "app" subdirectory (#1092)

Hopefully by explicitly configuring it to scan the "app" directory, it
will ignore the "infra/test" directory (which includes a whole Golang
dependency set that we don't really care to keep up-to-date).
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
FFS-3523: Give cbv_flows a unique device_id (#1085)

We've created a device_id field on the cbv_flow. This is sent along in a cookie, included in Mixpanel events, and in NewRelic logs.

Eventually, the goal will be to use this device_id to determine unique users. This PR is just the first step in that journey.
commits.author: Tim Miller

commits.message:
Delete `bin/current-region` script (#1082)

Jake [pointed out][1] that we could just use `aws configure get region`
instead of trying to parse the output, and it stuck with me. I keep
getting errors from the `bin/current-region` script, presumably because
I have a different `awscli` version than whatever runs in CI.

This commit replaces the script with the simple call to `aws configure
get`, which works regardless of `awscli` version.

[1]: https://github.com/DSACMS/iv-cbv-payroll/pull/1013#discussion_r2408903541
commits.author: Tom Dooner
